  "module": {
    "path": "src/agent/task",
    "name": "task",
    "purpose": "Owns agent task runtime. Task drives the per-task worker thread: it sends the initial status, triggers the initial plan through Step, routes task and step events, forwards execution events to execution_hub.route_event, and routes plan events to plan_hub.route_event. TaskState (state.rs) holds the session context, plan signature, user request, model backend, session event sender, plan_hub, an ExecutionHub that owns execution tracking, a monotonic step_count allocator that reserves contiguous step-number blocks, and the step WorkQueue, plus a manual Debug impl. Execution step spawning and event routing live in ExecutionHub, and execution-analysis plan triggering lives in Step.",
